</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="272A648180C1B37D4CC23B2028D67BE3" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B014BD25A91295D97C9CEB77FAC96389" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="796CB5656E0089378CC27E0E5AF87F3F" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName id="11BC8C55C5EC3E76E53C2CB60CAF73F1" authorityName="Choisy, Mem. Soc. Phys. Geneve 6: 477. 1834. (Choisy" authorityYear="1834" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rottlerianus" order="Solanales" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rottlerianus">
<emphasis id="68A2685BADD053E893E5C9F101A6E7AD" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Convolvulus rottlerianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only recently been found in Ethiopia and is unknown in Iran and Arabia. Ethiopian material was described as a separate species, 
<taxonomicName id="F621FB87EA17C0303C1CCD657B419958" authorityName="Sebsebe Demissew" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus gilbertii" order="Solanales" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gilbertii">
<emphasis id="1B80FA2C9C35FB1504D2BA1151031A22" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Convolvulus gilbertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably because the possibility of the occurrence of an Indian species was not considered. No difference between specimens from the two areas can be discerned. Little is known about the habitat of this subspecies in India but it is found in drier areas. In Ethiopia it is a rare plant of Acacia bushland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
